<section class="page-hero wrap">
  <p class="eyebrow">About Atelier Cygne</p>
  <h1 class="hed-lg" style="margin-top:16px;">A studio for looking<br>at rooms slowly.</h1>
  <p class="dek">Atelier Cygne began as a notebook of things worth noticing in the built world — a doorway, a stair rail, the way light sits in a stairwell at four in the afternoon. It became a monthly journal because some ideas need a whole edition to say properly.</p>
</section>

<section class="wrap">
  <div class="pillar-grid">
    <div>
      <p class="num">One</p>
      <h3>One Edition a Month</h3>
      <p>No daily feed, no scroll. A single, considered edition is published each month, meant to be read in one sitting or returned to across a week.</p>
    </div>
    <div>
      <p class="num">Two</p>
      <h3>Rooms Over Trends</h3>
      <p>We write about how spaces are actually inhabited — light, material, proportion, the way a house ages — rather than what's fashionable this season.</p>
    </div>
    <div>
      <p class="num">Three</p>
      <h3>Design &amp; Architecture, Together</h3>
      <p>The line between a building and the rooms inside it is mostly artificial. We cover both, because a chair and a stairwell are answering the same question.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

